dataIdInfo.idPurp: The Constituency boundaries were reviewed during the 2019 Delimitation of Constituencies in consultation with various district stakeholders namely; Mayors/Council Chairpersons, Members of Parliament, Ward Councilors, Chiefs, Traditional Leaders, Political Parties, Civil Society Organisations, Faith Based Organisations, School Zonal Managers, Women Organisations, Persons with Disabilities, Youth Organisations and the general Members of the Public. The shapefile will primarily assist the Electoral Commission of Zambia in the management of the Electoral Process. Some of the other notable organizations that will rely on the shapefile for their planning include the Zambia Statistics Agency, the National Assembly, Ministry of local Government, Local Councils and Non-governmental organizations just to mention but a few.

Consts.useLimit: This dataset has been officially endorsed by the Electoral Commission of Zambia. The shapefile will remain in use until the next Delimitation of Constituencies (revision of constituency boundaries) which will take place by the year 2029. The Constituency boundaries were generated at a scale of 1:10,000 and harmonized against the official district boundaries. The shapefile covers all the 10 provinces and 116 districts of the Republic of Zambia.

dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Constituency boundaries were generated within the confines of the National, Provincial and District boundaries andofficially endorsed by the Electoral Commission of Zambia
